rate heat, stirring occasionally, until softened and just beginning to brown, about 5 minutes.","ingredients":[{"id":11282,"name":"onion","localizedName":"onion","image":"brown-onion.png"}],"equipment":[],"length":{"number":5,"unit":"minutes"}},{"number":10,"step":"Add the ground spices and cook over low heat for 1 minute. Fold in the crabmeat, cilantro and lemon and lime juices and remove from the heat. Season with salt and pepper.","ingredients":[{"id":1102047,"name":"salt and pepper","localizedName":"salt and pepper","image":"salt-and-pepper.jpg"},{"id":11165,"name":"cilantro","localizedName":"cilantro","image":"cilantro.png"},{"id":10015136,"name":"crabmeat","localizedName":"crabmeat","image":"crabmeat.jpg"},{"id":2035,"name":"spices","localizedName":"spices","image":"spices.png"},{"id":9150,"name":"lemon","localizedName":"lemon","image":"lemon.png"},{"id":9159,"name":"lime","localizedName":"lime","image":"lime.jpg"}],"equipment":[],"length":{"number":1,"unit":"minutes"}},{"number":11,"step":"In each of 2 large nonstick skillets, heat 1 1/2 tablespoons of the remaining oil until shimmering. Season the snapper with salt and pepper; add to the skillets, skin side down. Cook over high heat, gently shaking the skillet, until the skin is golden brown and crisp, 5 minutes. Flip the fillets and cook for 2 minutes longer.","ingredients":[{"id":1102047,"name":"salt and pepper","localizedName":"salt and pepper","image":"salt-and-pepper.jpg"},{"id":15101,"name":"snapper","localizedName":"snapper","image":"snapper.jpg"},{"id":4582,"name":"cooking oil","localizedName":"cooking oil","image":"vegetable-oil.jpg"}],"equipment":[{"id":404645,"name":"frying pan","localizedName":"frying pan","image":"pan.png"}],"length":{"number":7,"unit":"minutes"}},{"number":12,"step":"Mound the spiced crab mixture in warmed shallow bowls and top with the snapper fillets, skin side up. Spoon the broth all around and serve right away.","ingredients":[{"id":15101,"name":"snapper fillets","localized